-- Siemens Sees ‘Significant’ Recovery at Renewables, Dpa-AFX Says
-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 2012-02-07T06:44:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-07/siemens-sees-significant-recovery-at-renewables-dpa-afx-says.html
Siemens AG  expects a “significant
improvement” at its renewable energy unit in coming quarters,
Dpa-AFX said, citing Chief Executive Officer  Peter Loescher .  Siemens, which posted a loss of 48 million euros ($63
million) at the unit in the three months through December, will
be one of the “big winners” from Germany’s change in energy
policy, Loescher said, according to the news service.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sheenagh Matthews in Frankfurt at 
